<HEAD>WASHINGTON WIRE: Bush Defeat Could Hand Dole New Platform</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LAWRENCE L. KNUTSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 If Vice President <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> stumbles on his way to the White House this November, erstwhile rival <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Dole </PERSON> could wind up as the nation's top <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> spokesman. The <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> minority leader under a Democratic administration could find himself playing the lead in a 1980s version of the 1960s Ev and <PERSON> Charlie </PERSON> <PERSON> Show </PERSON>. It might well be called the <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> and <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> show, with <PERSON> Dole </PERSON> being joined by <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Minority Leader <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> to counter a <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> president's programs and present alternatives to them. The Ev of Ev and <PERSON> Charlie </PERSON> was <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Minority leader <PERSON> Everett </PERSON> <PERSON> McKinley </PERSON> <PERSON> Dirksen </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION>. Dirksen teamed with <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Minority Leader <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Halleck </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> in a regular series of televised news conferences, <PERSON> Dirksen </PERSON> became the undisputed `` Mr. Republican'' of his era. <PERSON> Dole </PERSON>, crowded out of the 1988 Republican field by <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, has returned to his leadership position in the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>, serving notice he intends to prod the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> into opening its arms to a wider constituency. Republicans should, <PERSON> Dole </PERSON> says, address issues of concern to the homeless and the poor and embrace programs to deal with narcotics, day care, education, long-term health care, Medicaid and <ORGANIZATION> Medicare </ORGANIZATION>. `` We must, above all, give more Americans a reason to come our way and at the