 More of the <ORGANIZATION> Farmers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>'s rural development loans may be targeted to areas of high unemployment <ORGANIZATION> FmHA </ORGANIZATION> administrator <PERSON> Vance </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Clark </PERSON> said Monday a proposed rule change would direct a higher proportion of the agency's business and industrial loan guarantees to smaller companies where there is high unemployment. The `` B & amp; I'' program involves guarantees by FmHA on loans made by commercial lenders to provide jobs through new or expanded businesses in rural areas. Loan guarantees would range from 70 percent to 90 percent of the loan value, with the higher guarantee reserved for smaller loans. A spokesman, <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Neill </PERSON>, said <ORGANIZATION> B </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; I loan guarantees range up to $ 10 million per project. Those of up to $ 2 million would carry the 90 percent guarantee; $ 2 million to $ 5 million, 80 percent; and $ 5 million to $ 10 million, 70 percent, he said.
