<FIRST>r p PM-WISCONSINAt-A-Glance     04-05 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-WISCONSIN At-A-Glance,160</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here, at a glance, are the methods for picking delegates from <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION> to attend the 1988 Democratic and Republican national conventions this summer.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>DEMOCRATS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 Method: Primary Date: Tuesday, April 5 Pledged delegates: 81 Super delegates: 7 TOTAL: 88 Delegates allocated: Tuesday, April 5 Selection of delegates: Sunday, May 22 and Saturday, June 11 All of <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>'s 81 pledged delegates to the Democratic National Convention will be allocated among presidential candidates in proportion to the results of the primary on April 5.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>REPUBLICANS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 Method: Primary Date: Tuesday, April 5 Delegates: 47 Delegates allocated: Tuesday, April 5 Selection of delegates: Dates not yet determined. All of <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>'s delegates to the Republican National Convention will be allocated among presidential candidates based on the results of the primary. The presidential candidate receiving a plurality of votes in a congressional district will get all three of the national convention delegates from that district. The remaining 20 delegates at large will go to the presidential candidate receiving a plurality of the statewide vote. After the primary, the state committee will submit a list of national convention delegates for approval by the winning presidential candidates.
