<HEAD>With PM-Jackson and PM-US-Panama Rdp</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is the text of Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>'s letter to <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>, as released Monday by the <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> campaign. It was written in response to a March 23 letter from <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>. The text, as released by the campaign, contained several fragmentary sentences, misspellings, and other irregularities.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>Dear Reverend Jackson:</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 With sincere emotion, I read your most attentive letter, addressed to me, dated March 23, delivered by <PERSON> Cirilo </PERSON> <PERSON> McSween </PERSON>, in which you expressed your moral concern for the political and economic living conditions of the Panamanian people. Your concern for the crisis which has provoked great suffering and your appeal to me to persist in seeking peace and to put an end to this crisis, you expressed your anxiety to do whatever is possible to help alleviate the suffering and that we should act immediately. Your reputation as a great moral authority obligates me to give consideration and pay attention to your appeal, so that we may work together for the peace and unification of my country. In this sense, I manifest that it has always been one of the objectives of the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> and mine, to try to keep social peace for the Panamanian brothers and sisters and the foreigners that reside in our country. Our doctrine of National Security is inspired in the ideals of social justice and not of military concepts. I am sure that you are aware of the deep internal and external aspects of the political and economic situation now they have been destabalizing our consitutional Panamanian institutions so as to have a country that is weak and ruined, so it becomes an easy prey for the dictates of foreign forces. I am sure that you know the details of the amalgam between professional Panamanian politicians that are now dressed in sheepskin, and the legislative and executive sectors of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, who have translated an open and barefaced intervention into the internal affairs of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>, with the final proposition that they do not give compliment to the covenant of the Torrijos-Carter Treaty of 1977. No Panamanian with a firm nationalistic and patriotic sentiment would ever accept that the solution of internal problems of the Republic of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>, be dictated from <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION> -LRB- Consequently, I find it unnecesary to repeat this answer to your letter with more details in the wheel of the Panamanian crisis. There is something that has awakened my curiosity and come to my attention: How is it possible that the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s Administration who has publicly made gala of great love for God and have profound religious sentiment has campaigned terrible economic sanctions that have been imposed on the <LOCATION> Panamanian </LOCATION> people, causing the kind of suffering that you feel sincerely inhuman, causing the threat of brutal military forces, the sabotage, the psychological war against a materially small and weak country, but a dignified coungry, just like <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> is. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Solis </PERSON> <PERSON> Palma </PERSON> is the actual Head of State of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> by Constitutional decision of the <ORGANIZATION> Legislative </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION>; it is recognized by the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION>. He has recently called for a sincere national dialogue between all the sectors of the Panamanian society, with the purpose of a specific solution for the Democracy of our country, with up-coming celebration of free and open elections of May 1989. The Defense Forces support this cause by the Panamanian Chief of State and at the same time, reject any imposition and any political and economic program that will be dictated from <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> D.C </ORGANIZATION>. The word, `` perpetuity'' has been historically imposed on <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> by the <LOCATION> Unied </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> in the different Canal Treaties since 1903. Nevertheless, I assure you that, those words do not form a part of my personal vocabulary, nor of my honor in the military. My duration as Commander and Chief of the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forces </ORGANIZATION> is governed by the Panamanian Constitution and Law of the Defense Forces. You can do a lot to help, by eliminating one of the principal causes of the suffering of many Panamanians. In other words, the foreign intervention. You may contribute by your knowledgeable advice and create by mutual communition, the harmony and the material peace between all Panamanians, without discrimination of any class. With my deepest respect for you, I shall be at your disposition to speak with you more deeply about this theme whenever you are available. Attentively, P.S. I have been lied about! I have been villafied! I have been humiliated internationally! I consider myself to have been persecuted by illegal actions by so-called justice, by political interests of your nation. I, as a Christian, before you, denounce this untrue, because how is it possible that nation as powerful should employ the services of journalistic mis-information, the threat of death bdfore one of God's children, such as I consider to be at the present time in this struggle? This is my testimony, <PERSON> Reverend </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>, before the Divine and Eternal Laws of the all-powerful God. I feel rich in faith and find my situation in <ORGANIZATION> Isaiah </ORGANIZATION> 45, with all humility and reverence.
</TEXT>
