<HEAD>Wright Adviser Details Effort To Sell Weapons To Contras</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RITA BEAMISH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An adviser to House Speaker <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Wright </PERSON> says he contacted <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> North </PERSON> associate <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> nearly two years ago in a bid to broker a weapons deal for the Contras but did not know he was tapping into the North private aid network. In a deposition taken by congressional Iran-Contra investigators and released Monday, <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Pena </PERSON> said that he only met <PERSON> North </PERSON> once briefly and that <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> `` may have mentioned'' North. He said he had a sense that <PERSON> Miller </PERSON>, a public relations man with ties to the Contras, might be able to get a weapons offer to them and so <PERSON> Pena </PERSON> asked him about the possibility in the spring of 1986. <PERSON> Wright </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> Democrat and longstanding opponent of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military aid to the Contras, has said he had no idea his friend and adviser was trying to sell them weapons. <PERSON> Pena </PERSON>, a former <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Affairs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> staff member, has traveled to <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> as <PERSON> Wright </PERSON>'s observer and emissary in the evolving peace process between the U.S.-backed Contras and the leftist Nicaraguan government. North is charged in the Iran-Contra affair on a variety of counts stemming from his clandestine operation to supply the Contras. <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> named <PERSON> North </PERSON> as a co-conspirator when <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> pleaded guilty to illegally using a tax-exempt foundation for the non-exempt purpose of raising money to arm the Contras. Rep. <PERSON> Dante </PERSON> <PERSON> Fascell </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Fla </LOCATION>., the vice chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATI