't always win. Politics is not my favorite pastime.'' <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> ran for governor five times before being elected in 1986. Although <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>'s son, <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON>, testified last week that their <LOCATION> Mecham </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pontiac </LOCATION> dealership in suburban <LOCATION> Glendale </LOCATION> was thriving, he announced a day later that they'd been forced to sell it for $ 4 million because of dwindling sales. <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON> <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> said bad publicity surrounding his father's political battles had driven customers away The dealership was sold last week.
