<HEAD>Convicted Kidnapper Could Be `Marked Man' As Parole Ends</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Convicted kidnapper <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> Parnell </PERSON> will be a `` marked man'' if he decides to return to <LOCATION> Mendocino </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, where he was arrested for holding two boys captive eight years ago, a county official said. `` Let him go to some other state. Let him stay away from this county. There's still hard feelings here,'' <LOCATION> Mendocino </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Supervisor <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Cimolino </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corrections </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Gore </PERSON> said <PERSON> Parnell </PERSON> is to be discharged from parole today, but that his office was not aware of any protest over the action. <PERSON> Parnell </PERSON>, 56, was paroled to <LOCATION> Alameda </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> in the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION> area after serving five years in prison for kidnapping <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Stayner </PERSON>, then 7, from <LOCATION> Merced </LOCATION> on Dec. 4, 1972, and <PERSON> Timothy </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON>, then 5, from <LOCATION> Ukiah </LOCATION> on Valentine's Day in 1980. Both boys were abducted while walking home from school. Although <PERSON> Stayner </PERSON> said <PERSON> Parnell </PERSON> regularly sexually abused him, charges of child abuse against <PERSON> Parnell </PERSON> were dismissed in 1981 when a state appeals court said the statute of limitations had expired. Word of <PERSON> Parnell </PERSON>'s release angered <PERSON> Stayner </PERSON>, who said he ca n't forgive him During the trial, <PERSON> Stayner </PERSON> testified that <PERSON> Parnell </PERSON> ordered him to call him `` Dad,'' renamed him <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON> <PERSON> Parnell </PERSON> and told people <PERSON> Sta