Shultz</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Shultz, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAIRO, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A leading government-owned newspaper today criticized <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> leaders in the Israeli-occupied territories for boycotting Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>'s efforts for <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> peace. `` We would have preferred if they -LRB- Palestinian leaders -RRB- revised their continued boycott and tried to give a chance for a dialogue with the American side,'' an editorial in the daily <ORGANIZATION> Al-Akhbar </ORGANIZATION> said. The newspaper said <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> began talks with Palestinians last month when he met in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> with <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> professors <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Said </PERSON> and <PERSON> Ibrahim </PERSON> <PERSON> Abu </PERSON> <PERSON> Lughud </PERSON>, who belong to the legislative arm of the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> movement to establish a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> state on <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> territory. It said <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>'s shuttle visits `` to the parties of the <LOCATION> Arab-Israeli </LOCATION> conflict -LRB- are -RRB- ... indications of the seriousness of -LRB- President -RRB- <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s administration to reach a final settlemenmt of the region's problem.'' `` It is true that the American initiative does not meet all the desires of the Arab side in general and the Palestinians in particular, but this does not mean it is devoid of any positive elements that could be built on and promoted during the dialogue,'' the newspaper said. It said the initiative has for the first time recognized the right of the Palestinians for self-rule and called this a `` turning point in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>'s policy.'' The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> plan calls for three years of self-rule, but not statehood, for the 1.5 million Palestinians living in the occupied territories. Negotiations on an overall settlement would open in December. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> captured the <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> in the 1967 <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> war. For the last four months anti-occupation rioting by Palestinians in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> has killed more than 135 Arabs.
