<DATELINE>MOUNDSVILLE, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Three convicted killers who escaped from the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> Pententiary are `` probably several states away by now,'' a state prison official said today. `` There's been no news on them, whatsover,'' said Corrections Commissioner A.V. <PERSON> Dodrill </PERSON>. `` We're not searching any areas around the prison. `` Information has been given to other police agencies in the area, and they are checking that out. What it boils down to is routine police work.'' Authorities in <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> also reported no trace of the three, who broke through an elevator shaft and used bolt cutters to escape Sunday night. Police immediately gave protection to those who helped convict one of the three, <PERSON> Bobby </PERSON> <PERSON> Stacy </PERSON>, including a <LOCATION> Columbus </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, woman who testified against him. The woman, a former friend of <PERSON> Stacy </PERSON>'s, received death threats and her car was burned during his trial. <PERSON> Stacy </PERSON>, 35, was convicted of killing a police officer and accused of shooting another. Authorities say he had vowed to kill the prosecutor and circuit judge who had put him behind bars. `` He is educated and cold-blooded. That's the worst combination there is,'' said <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Hatcher </PERSON>, an assistant <LOCATION> Cabell </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> prosecutor and one of those <PERSON> Stacy </PERSON> threatened to kill. `` My fear is that some police officer is going to get killed, because that's this guy's method. <PERSON> Hatcher </PERSON> said he had no plans to ask for protection for himself, but <ORGANIZATION> Cabell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> Judge <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ferguson </PERSON> asked that an extra bailiff be assigned to him. <PERSON> Sta