<FIRST>r f PM-BusinessHighlights 2Takes   04-05 0492</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Business Highlights, 2 Takes,0515</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 F.W. <ORGANIZATION> Woolworth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> has received notice that <ORGANIZATION> Dart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> intends to acquire a substantial amount of the stock in the nation's 13th largest retailer. <ORGANIZATION> Woolworth </ORGANIZATION>, which built its reputation in the five-and-dime store business before expanding into specialty retailing, responded to <PERSON> Dart </PERSON>'s move with the adoption by its board of a `` poison-pill'' takeover defense. The retailer said in a statement Monday it was notified a partnership controlled by <PERSON> Dart </PERSON> Chairman <PERSON> Herbert </PERSON> <PERSON> Haft </PERSON> had filed with federal antitrust officials documents indicating the group intended to acquire $ 15 million or more of <ORGANIZATION> Woolworth </ORGANIZATION>'s stock.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the filmmaker that was sold and then bought back by financier <PERSON> Kirk </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON>, says it has received several takeover proposals, and plans to create a special committee of directors to study them. <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>'s chairman and chief executive, <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Rich </PERSON>, declined to identify the suitors in Monday's announcement. But analysts suggested that <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON>, who owns 79 percent of the company's 50.1 million shares, may be seeking to take <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> private.
</TEXT>
